<b>Joseph Bastianich</b> (born 1968) is an American restaurateur.  He is the son of chef <chef wordnetid="109963574" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../051/2336051.xml">
Lidia Bastianich</link></chef>
 and a frequent business partner of <chef wordnetid="109963574" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../973/666973.xml">
Mario Batali</link></chef>
, with whom he owns several <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../042/645042.xml">
New York City</link></village>
 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../437/26437.xml">
restaurants</link>.  <p>

Prior to entering the restaurant and wine indistry, Bastianich graduated from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../811/239811.xml">
Boston College</link></university>
 and worked as a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../737/60737.xml">
bond</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../542/4788542.xml">
trader</link> at <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../710/243710.xml">
Merrill Lynch</link></company>
. </p>
<p>

